-- Water to Australian Irrigators Should Be Cut 27-37 Percent, Report Says
-- B y   G e m m a   D a l e y
-- 2010-10-08T05:07:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-08/water-to-australian-irrigators-should-be-cut-27-37-percent-report-says.html
Water to irrigators should be cut by
between 27 percent and 37 percent, or 3,000 to 4,000 gigaliters,
and diverted to the environment, which would cost the government
as much as A$4 billion ($3.9 billion), the Murray-Darling Basin
Authority said in a report released in Canberra today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gemma Daley at 
 gdaley@bloomberg.net  